'''Gebeleizis''' (or ''Gebeleixis'', ''Nebeleizis'') was a god worshiped by the [[Getae]], probably related to the [[Thracians|Thracian]] god of storm and lightning, [[Zibelthiurdos]].<ref>Tomashek, ''Die Alten Thraker'', II, page 62</ref> He was represented as a handsome man, sometimes wearing a beard. The lightning and [[thunder]] were his manifestations. According to [[Herodotus]], some [[Getae]] equated Gebeleizis with [[Zalmoxis]] as the same god.

