{{Infobox mountain | name = Le Boudri | other_name = Burgihorn | photo = Le Boudri - Depuis Sorebois.jpg | photo_caption = View from the [[Corne de Sorebois]] (west side) | elevation_m = 3070 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 100 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps and [[Google Earth]]. The key col is located south of the summit at 2,970 metres.</ref> | parent_peak = [[Hirsihorn]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Pennine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|11|33.6|N|7|39|31.8|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Le Boudri''' (also known as ''Burgihorn'') is a [[mountain]] of the Swiss [[Pennine Alps]], located east of [[Ayer, Switzerland|Ayer]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. It lies between the valleys of [[Anniviers]] and [[Turtmanntal|Turtmann]], north of the [[Hirsihorn]].
