{{Infobox Union |name= SARTUC |country= |affiliation= |members= |full_name= South Asian Regional Trade Union Council |native_name= |image= |founded= 1988 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= |people= |website= |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. --> The '''South Asian Regional Trade Union Council (SARTUC)''' is a [[federation]] of [[national trade union center]]s whose geographic scope covers South Asia. SARTUC's mission is to promote workers' rights within its member nations.<ref>[http://www.gurn.info/topic/trade/icftu_0604.pdf International Confederation of Free Trade Unions. ''The Spread of Bilateral and Regional Trade Agreements.'' June 2004.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208160035/http://www.gurn.info/topic/trade/icftu_0604.pdf |date=2006-12-08 }}</ref>
The South Asian Regional Trade Union Council was formed in January 1988 by some of the affiliates of the [[International Confederation of Free Trade Unions]] (now the [[ITUC]]) in countries belonging to the [[South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation]] (SAARC)—[[Afghanistan]], [[Bangladesh]], [[Bhutan]], [[India]], [[Maldives]], [[Nepal]], [[Pakistan]] and [[Sri Lanka]]. The Indian trade union center [[Indian National Trade Union Congress]] and [[Hind Mazdoor Sabha]], were the founding members of SARTUC.<ref>[http://www-old.itcilo.org/actrav/english/calendar/2001/A3_2380/work/Country_reports/india.doc Pijush Chakraborty. "Trade Union Training on Information Technology." Hind Mazdoor Sabha. Turin/Vienna: February 19, 2001–March 16, 2001.]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Nazrul Islam Khan (then-president of the Bangladesh Metal Workers' Federation) was SAR-TUC's general-secretary in 2003.<ref>[http://www.ilo.org/public/english/region/asro/bangkok/public/releases/yr2003/pr0326.htm "Shipbreaking Guidelines Charting New Waters." ''ILO News.'' October 15, 2003.]</ref>
